### Goal
Determine the appropriate response level based on occurrence count and severity.

### Implementation: src/response.rs
```rust
pub fn determine_response(
    occurrences: &OccurrenceStats,
    severity: Severity,
    config: &ResponseConfig,
) -> ResponseLevel {
    // Check severity override for starting level
    let start_level = config
        .severity_overrides
        .get(&severity)
        .map(|c| c.start_at)
        .unwrap_or(ResponseLevel::Warn);

    // Check severity override for max level
    let max_level = config
        .severity_overrides
        .get(&severity)
        .map(|c| c.max_level)
        .unwrap_or(ResponseLevel::HardBlock);

    // Determine level based on occurrences
    let level = match occurrences.total {
        0 => start_level,
        1 => ResponseLevel::Warn.max(start_level),
        2 => ResponseLevel::SoftBlock.max(start_level),
        _ => ResponseLevel::HardBlock,
    };

    // Cap at max level
    level.min(max_level)
}
```

### Edge Cases
- No history (first time) → start_level
- History from before window → treated as first time
- Bypass in history → counts toward escalation
- Allowlisted after blocks → reset or continue?

